.TH "drm_ioctl_flags" 9 "drm_ioctl_flags" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_ioctl_flags \- Check for core ioctl and return ioctl permission flags
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" drm_ioctl_flags
.BI "(unsigned int nr "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nr" 12
ioctl number
.IP "flags" 12
where to return the ioctl permission flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This ioctl is only used by the vmwgfx driver to augment the access checks
done by the drm core and insofar a pretty decent layering violation. This
shouldn't be used by any drivers.
.SH "RETURN"
True if the \fInr\fP corresponds to a DRM core ioctl number, false otherwise.
